'''Mariwan Halabjaee''' ({{lang-ku-2|<U+0645><U+0647><U+0631><U+06CC><U+0648><U+0627><U+0646> <U+0647><U+0647><U+06B5><U+0647><U+0628><U+062C><U+0647><U+06CC><U+06CC>}}, ''{{lang|ku|Her<U+00EA>m<U+00EE> Kurdistan}}'')<ref group="note">Alternate spellings: Mariwan, Marywan, Marewan / Halabjaee, Halabjay, Halabjayee, Halabjaye, Halabjayi, Halabjai.</ref> (born 1 August 1963) is the [[Iraqi Kurdistan|Iraqi Kurdish]] author of the book ''Sex, Sharia and Women in the History of Islam'' (alternate title: ''Sex, Legislation and Women in Islamic History'').<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sites.google.com/site/charlesrcblog/home |title= Sex, Sharia and Women in the History of Islam |author= Halabjaee, Mariwan|date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> The book is about how [[Islam]] and [[Sharia]] are allegedly used to oppress [[Muslim]] women. "I wanted to prove how oppressed women are in [[Islam]] and that they have no rights," said Halabjaee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/152645 |title= Mark Thomas flushes out a fatwa |author= Mark Thomas|date= 27 February 2006|work= New Statesman|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> Halabjaee asserted the book was, "based on [[Islam]]ic sources such as the Holy [[Quran]], [[Muslim]] and [[Sahih al-Bukhari|Bukhari books]]<ref group="note">See also [[Muhammad al-Bukhari]].</ref> and many more."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref>

==First fatwa in Iraqi Kurdistan==
Halabjaee was reportedly forced to flee from [[Iraqi Kurdistan]] to Norway because the [[Islamic Kurdish League|Islamic League of Kurdistan]] issued a "conditional" [[fatwa]] to kill him if he did not repent and apologize for writing his book.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.kurdmedia.com/article.aspx?id=11809 |title= The `Salman Rushdie of Iraqi-Kurdistan` forced to flee to Sweden |author= |date= 29 March 2006|work= Kurdish Media|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> Halabjaee reported, "the [[mullah]]s and scholars said if I go to them and apologize they will give me 80 lashes and then refer me to the fatwa committee to decide if I am to be beheaded. They might forgive me, they might not."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/152645 |title= Mark Thomas flushes out a fatwa |author= Mark Thomas|date= 27 February 2006|work= New Statesman|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.kurdmedia.com/article.aspx?id=11809 |title= The `Salman Rushdie of Iraqi-Kurdistan` forced to flee to Sweden |author= |date= 29 March 2006|work= Kurdish Media|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

Halabjaee allegedly received telephone calls saying, "Now, in 10 years or 15 years, we will kill you."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> Another time, Halabjaee reported, "the [[Islamism|Islamists]] said once from the radio, if they found out where I was, they would blow themselves up with me."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/152645 |title= Mark Thomas flushes out a fatwa |author= Mark Thomas|date= 27 February 2006|work= New Statesman|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> "With that book I wanted to defend women but the first thing I did was hurt my wife," said Halabjaee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> As a result, Halabjaee went into hiding with his pregnant wife and three children.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref>

Halabjaee fled [[Iraqi Kurdistan]] after the [[Kurdistan Regional Government]] (KRG) allegedly refused to offer him any protection or to arrest those who threatened his life. "The Kurdish authorities have not provided any protection from threats and [[fatwa]]s," said Halabjaee, "any moment I am expecting a bullet or a hand grenade to be thrown into where I live."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/node/152645 |title= Mark Thomas flushes out a fatwa |author= Mark Thomas|date= 27 February 2006|work= New Statesman|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2008/1/kurdlocal472.htm |title= "The Salman Rushdie of Iraqi Kurdistan" sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 9, 2008|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref>

In response to the Halabjaee affair, the [[Kurdistan Regional Government|KRG]] [[Kurdistan Regional Government#Parliament|Minister of Religious Issues]], Dr. Mohammad Gaznayi, told protestors that according to the law of [[Iraqi Kurdistan]], "defamation" or "criticizing" religion or religious figures is a crime and its punishment is severe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2006/3/kurdlocal131.htm |title= The "Salman Rushdie of Iraqi-Kurdistan" forced to flee to Sweden |author= |date= March 29, 2006|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> "We will give those who attack our prophets a sentence so that they can be a lesson for everyone," said Dr. Gaznayi.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kurdmedia.com/article.aspx?id=11809 |title= The `Salman Rushdie of Iraqi-Kurdistan` forced to flee to Sweden |author= |date= 29 March 2006|work= Kurdish Media|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref group="note">Dr. Mohammad Gaznayi is the same KRG Minister of Religious Issues who said, "I consider that those who turn to Christianity pose a threat to society." See {{cite web |url=http://www.rferl.org/content/article/1059651.html |title= Iraq: Christians Face Threats From All Sides |author= Kathleen Ridolfo|date= July 3, 2005 |work= Radio Free Europe / Radio Liberty|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}; {{cite web |url=http://iwpr.net/report-news/kurdish-christians-complain-discrimination |title= Kurdish Christians Complain of Discrimination |author= Ayyub Kareem|date= November 17, 2005 |work= Institute for War & Peace Reporting|publisher= |accessdate= 10 June 2012}}.  Dr. Gaznayi also said people who turn to Christianity are <U+201C>renegades<U+201D> in the eyes of Islam. See {{cite web |url=http://iwpr.net/report-news/kurdish-christians-complain-discrimination |title= Kurdish Christians Complain of Discrimination |author= Ayyub Kareem|date= November 17, 2005 |work= Institute for War & Peace Reporting|publisher= |accessdate= 12 June 2012}}.</ref> Halabjaee was in possession of a warrant for his arrest issued by the [[Suleimaniya]] police department when he fled [[Iraqi Kurdistan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekurd.net/mismas/articles/misc2006/3/kurdlocal131.htm |title= The "Salman Rushdie of Iraqi-Kurdistan" forced to flee to Sweden |author= |date= March 29, 2006|work= Kurd Net|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.no/nyheter/lokalt/Fryktar-for-livet-i-Noreg-1838331.html |title= Fryktar for livet i Noreg |author= Njord V. Svendsen|date= March 19, 2007|work= BT.NO|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}.</ref>

In August 2006, Halabjaee was granted political asylum in Norway.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.idag.no/aktuelt-oppslag.php3?ID=12314 |title= Lever i skjul etter islam-kritikk |author= Bjarte Ysteb<U+00F8>|date= March 19, 2007|work= IDAG|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.no/nyheter/lokalt/Fryktar-for-livet-i-Noreg-1838331.html |title= Fryktar for livet i Noreg |author= Njord V. Svendsen|date= March 19, 2007|work= BT.NO|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.rights.no/publisher/publisher.asp?id=36&tekstid=1374 |title= Norskiraner d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi i Irak |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Human Rights Service|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref>

==Conviction in absentia for blashphemy==
In December 2007, Halabjaee was convicted in absentia in [[Iraqi Kurdistan]] for the crime of [[blasphemy]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2008/01/08/Author-sentenced-to-jail-for-blasphemy/UPI-79101199838545/ |title= Author sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= UPI|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/Forfatter-bosatt-i-Norge-domt-for-blasfemi-6503293.html |title= Forfatter bosatt i Norge d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.no/bergenpuls/litteratur/Domt-forfatter-far-stotte-1874344.html |title= D<U+00F8>mt forfatter f<U+00E5>r st<U+00F8>tte |author= |date= January 25, 2008|work= Bt.No|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.rights.no/publisher/publisher.asp?id=36&tekstid=1374 |title= Norskiraner d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi i Irak |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Human Rights Service|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> A court in [[Halabja]] sentenced Halabjaee to prison for writing that the prophet Mohammed had 19 wives, married a 9-year-old when he was 54 years old, and committed murder and rape.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2008/01/08/Author-sentenced-to-jail-for-blasphemy/UPI-79101199838545/ |title= Author sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= UPI|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/Forfatter-bosatt-i-Norge-domt-for-blasfemi-6503293.html |title= Forfatter bosatt i Norge d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.no/bergenpuls/litteratur/Domt-forfatter-far-stotte-1874344.html |title= D<U+00F8>mt forfatter f<U+00E5>r st<U+00F8>tte |author= |date= January 25, 2008|work= Bt.No|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.rights.no/publisher/publisher.asp?id=36&tekstid=1374 |title= Norskiraner d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi i Irak |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Human Rights Service|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref> Halabjaee remains in Norway. The sentence states that he will be arrested upon his return to [[Iraqi Kurdistan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2008/01/08/Author-sentenced-to-jail-for-blasphemy/UPI-79101199838545/ |title= Author sentenced to jail for blasphemy |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= UPI|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/Forfatter-bosatt-i-Norge-domt-for-blasfemi-6503293.html |title= Forfatter bosatt i Norge d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.bt.no/bergenpuls/litteratur/Domt-forfatter-far-stotte-1874344.html |title= D<U+00F8>mt forfatter f<U+00E5>r st<U+00F8>tte |author= |date= January 25, 2008|work= Bt.No|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.rights.no/publisher/publisher.asp?id=36&tekstid=1374 |title= Norskiraner d<U+00F8>mt for blasfemi i Irak |author= |date= January 8, 2008|work= Human Rights Service|publisher= |accessdate=22 April 2012}}</ref>

==Second fatwa in Norway==
In September 2008, [[Mullah Krekar]] allegedly threatened to kill Halabjaee in an audio file published on the Kurdish website Renesans.nu. "I swear that we will not live if you live. Either you go before us, or we go before you," said Krekar.<ref>{{YouTube|id=Duww2LoEdVU|title=Renesans.nu&nbsp;<U+2013> Mariwan Halabjaee Threatened by Mullah Krekar}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article2677263.ece |title= Mener forfatter fortjener d<U+00F8>dsstraff |author= Kristian Aale|date= 27 Sep 2008|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/2008/09/27/548371.html |title= Krekar drapstruet meg |author= Martine Aurdal, Tore Gjerstad|date= 27 September 2008|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.namdalsavisa.no/Innenriks/article3813132.ece |title= Krekar hardt ut mot forfatter|author= |date= 27 September 2008|work= Namdalsavisa.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.vg.no/nyheter/utenriks/artikkel.php?artid=530601 |title= Krekar mener forfatter fortjener d<U+00F8>dsstraff&nbsp;<U+2013> Vi forbyr oss selv livet dersom du lever|author= |date= 27 September 2008|work= VG.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> [[Mullah Krekar]] was the original leader of the Islamist terrorist group [[Ansar al-Islam]].<ref>See [[Ansar al-Islam#History|Ansar_al-Islam - History]]</ref> [[Mullah Krekar]] compared Halabjaee with [[Salman Rushdie]] and [[Ayaan Hirsi Ali]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article2677263.ece |title= Mener forfatter fortjener d<U+00F8>dsstraff |author= Kristian Aale|date= 27 Sep 2008|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/2008/09/27/548371.html |title= Krekar drapstruet meg |author= Martine Aurdal, Tore Gjerstad|date= 27 September 2008|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.namdalsavisa.no/Innenriks/article3813132.ece |title= Krekar hardt ut mot forfatter|author= |date= 27 September 2008|work= Namdalsavisa.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.vg.no/nyheter/utenriks/artikkel.php?artid=530601 |title= Krekar mener forfatter fortjener d<U+00F8>dsstraff&nbsp;<U+2013> Vi forbyr oss selv livet dersom du lever|author= |date= 27 September 2008|work= VG.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> [[Mullah Krekar]], like Halabjaee, currently resides in Norway as a refugee. Since February 2003, [[Mullah Krekar]] has had an expulsion order against him in Norway. The order has been suspended, however, pending Iraqi government guarantees that [[Mullah Krekar]] will not face torture or execution.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/article2677263.ece |title= Mener forfatter fortjener d<U+00F8>dsstraff |author= Kristian Aale|date= 27 Sep 2008|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/nyheter/2008/09/27/548371.html |title= Krekar drapstruet meg |author= Martine Aurdal, Tore Gjerstad|date= 27 September 2008|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.namdalsavisa.no/Innenriks/article3813132.ece |title= Krekar hardt ut mot forfatter|author= |date= 27 September 2008|work= Namdalsavisa.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.vg.no/nyheter/utenriks/artikkel.php?artid=530601 |title= Krekar mener forfatter fortjener d<U+00F8>dsstraff&nbsp;<U+2013> Vi forbyr oss selv livet dersom du lever|author= |date= 27 September 2008|work= VG.no|publisher= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref>

In February 2012, [[Mullah Krekar]] confirmed in the [[Oslo District Court]] that he had issued a twenty page [[fatwa]] against Halabjaee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/02/17/nyheter/krekar/trusler/terrorisme/politiets_sikkerhetstjeneste/20283255/ |title= Jeg frykter hele tida at noen skal komme bakfra og drepe meg|author= Harald S. Klungtveit|date= 17 February 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/jeg-kommer-til-aa-halshugge-deg-uansett-hvor-du-er-3716605.html |title= Jeg kommer til <U+00E5> halshugge deg, uansett hvor du er |author= Eivind Fondenes|date= 23 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/krim/vil-ha-fem-aars-fengsel-for-krekar-3719633.html |title= Vil ha fem <U+00E5>rs fengsel for Krekar|author= Kjell Persen|date= 28 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/denne-koranbrenningen-fikk-krekar-til-aa-utstede-fatwa-mot-to-kurdere-3717058.html |title= Denne koranbrenningen fikk Krekar til <U+00E5> utstede fatwa mot to kurdere|author= Eivind Fondenes|date= 25 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://m.nrk.no/m/artikkel.jsp?art_id=18000500 |title= Avsa d<U+00F8>dsdom mot forfatter|author= Anders Brekke|date= 17 February 2012|work= NRK.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://debatt.sol.no/content/krekar-utsteder-dodsdommer |title= Krekar utsteder d<U+00F8>dsdommer|author= Lilla Puddel|date= 17 February 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> The [[fatwa]] was sent to several hundred [[Islam]]ic scholars around the world. While [[Mullah Krekar]] said he thought he might be able to "guarantee the safety" of Halabjaee, [[Mullah Krekar]] confirmed that his [[fatwa]] "implies" that it is "permissible" to kill Halabjaee in [[Oslo]] or anywhere else.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/02/17/nyheter/krekar/trusler/terrorisme/politiets_sikkerhetstjeneste/20283255/ |title= Jeg frykter hele tida at noen skal komme bakfra og drepe meg|author= Harald S. Klungtveit|date= 17 February 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/jeg-kommer-til-aa-halshugge-deg-uansett-hvor-du-er-3716605.html |title= Jeg kommer til <U+00E5> halshugge deg, uansett hvor du er |author= Eivind Fondenes|date= 23 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/krim/vil-ha-fem-aars-fengsel-for-krekar-3719633.html |title= Vil ha fem <U+00E5>rs fengsel for Krekar|author= Kjell Persen|date= 28 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/denne-koranbrenningen-fikk-krekar-til-aa-utstede-fatwa-mot-to-kurdere-3717058.html |title= Denne koranbrenningen fikk Krekar til <U+00E5> utstede fatwa mot to kurdere|author= Eivind Fondenes|date= 25 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://m.nrk.no/m/artikkel.jsp?art_id=18000500 |title= Avsa d<U+00F8>dsdom mot forfatter|author= Anders Brekke|date= 17 February 2012|work= NRK.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://debatt.sol.no/content/krekar-utsteder-dodsdommer |title= Krekar utsteder d<U+00F8>dsdommer|author= Lilla Puddel|date= 17 February 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> [[Mullah Krekar]] compared Halabjaee to [[Theo van Gogh (film director)|Theo van Gogh]], the film director who was killed by an [[Islamist]] in the [[Netherlands]] in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/02/17/nyheter/krekar/trusler/terrorisme/politiets_sikkerhetstjeneste/20283255/ |title= Jeg frykter hele tida at noen skal komme bakfra og drepe meg|author= Harald S. Klungtveit|date= 17 February 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/jeg-kommer-til-aa-halshugge-deg-uansett-hvor-du-er-3716605.html |title= Jeg kommer til <U+00E5> halshugge deg, uansett hvor du er |author= Eivind Fondenes|date= 23 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/krim/vil-ha-fem-aars-fengsel-for-krekar-3719633.html |title= Vil ha fem <U+00E5>rs fengsel for Krekar|author= Kjell Persen|date= 28 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2.no/nyheter/innenriks/denne-koranbrenningen-fikk-krekar-til-aa-utstede-fatwa-mot-to-kurdere-3717058.html |title= Denne koranbrenningen fikk Krekar til <U+00E5> utstede fatwa mot to kurdere|author= Eivind Fondenes|date= 25 February 2012|work= TV2.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://m.nrk.no/m/artikkel.jsp?art_id=18000500 |title= Avsa d<U+00F8>dsdom mot forfatter|author= Anders Brekke|date= 17 February 2012|work= NRK.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://debatt.sol.no/content/krekar-utsteder-dodsdommer |title= Krekar utsteder d<U+00F8>dsdommer|author= Lilla Puddel|date= 17 February 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

On 26 March 2012, [[Mullah Krekar]] was sentenced to 5 years in prison for making death threats.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/27/world/europe/norway-cleric-sentenced-for-threats.html?_r=2&scp=8&sq=Norwegian&st=cse |title= Norway: Cleric Sentenced for Threats|author= The Associated Press|date= 27 March 2012|work= The New York Times|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}<br />*{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/03/27/nyheter/mulla_krekar/pst/varetekt/innenriks/20865736/ |title= PST <U+00F8>nsker <U+00E5> ha ham sittende bak l<U+00E5>s og sl<U+00E5> til lagmannsrettssaken|author= Gunnar Hult Green|date= 27 March 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> He appealed. On 26 March 2012, [[Mullah Krekar]] was re-arrested for making threats against two Kurds and the Conservative Party leader [[Erna Solberg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2012/03/27/nyheter/mulla_krekar/pst/varetekt/innenriks/20865736/ |title= PST <U+00F8>nsker <U+00E5> ha ham sittende bak l<U+00E5>s og sl<U+00E5> til lagmannsrettssaken|author= Gunnar Hult Green|date= 27 March 2012|work= Dagbladet.no|publisher= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

On 6 December 2012, the Court of Appeal acquitted [[Mullah Krekar]] of charges of incitement to terrorism, but found [[Mullah Krekar|Krekar]] guilty of four counts of intimidation under aggravating circumstances.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/Mullah-Krekar-fikk-redusert-straff-i-lagmannsretten-7063523.html |title= Mullah Krekar fikk redusert straff i lagmannsretten|author= Svend Ole Kvilesj<U+00F8> , Lene Li Dragland|date= 6 December 2012|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=9 December 2012}}</ref> The Court of Appeal ordered that [[Mullah Krekar|Krekar]] pay 130,000 kroner in damages compensation to each of the three Kurds he threatened, and to serve two years and ten months in prison, less the 255 days he was in custody.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aftenposten.no/nyheter/iriks/Mullah-Krekar-fikk-redusert-straff-i-lagmannsretten-7063523.html |title= Mullah Krekar fikk redusert straff i lagmannsretten|author= Svend Ole Kvilesj<U+00F8> , Lene Li Dragland|date= 6 December 2012|work= Aftenposten|publisher= |accessdate=9 December 2012}}</ref>

